pink flowers =9

questions.text: The fifth part of a number when increased by 5 equals its fourth part decreased by 5. Find the number.
questions.solution:
let the number be x

$\frac{x}{5}+5\:=\frac{x}{4}-5$  

$\frac{x}{5}-\frac{x}{4}=-5-5$  

$\frac{x}{5}-\frac{x}{4}=-10$  

$\frac{4x-5x}{20}=-10$  

$\frac{-x}{20}=-10$  

$-x=-10\times20$  

-x=-200

x=200

the number is 200

steps.step:
−x=−10×20−x=−10×20

x=200

questions.text: A dealer bought 18 chairs for ₹300 each. He sold 12 of them at ₹400 each and 6 of them at ₹250 each. Find his gain or loss percent.
questions.solution:
cost of 18 chairs @ Rs 300

$=18\times300\\=5400\\cp=5400$  

12chairs @ Rs 400

$=12\times400\\=Rs\:4800$  

6 chairs @ Rs 250

$=6\times250\\=Rs\:1500\\sp=4800+1500\\sp=Rs\:6300\\\\sp>cp\:\:gain\%\\gain\:\%=\frac{gain}{cp}\times100\\gain\:=sp-cp\\gain=6300-5400\\gain\:=900\\$  

$gain\%=\frac{900}{5400}\times100$  

$gain\%=\frac{50}{3}\%=16\frac{2}{3}\%$

questions.text: Chalk contains 3% carbon, 10% calcium and 12% oxygen. Find the amount in grams of each of these substances in 1kg chalk.
questions.solution:
1 kg =1000 gms

Amount in grams

$carbon=\frac{3}{100}\times1000$  

               =30gms

$calcium=\frac{10}{100}\times1000$  

                 =100gms

$oxygen\:=\frac{12}{100}\times1000$  

                 =120gms

 The amount of carbon, calcium and oxygen of in 1kg of chalk is 30gms,100gms and 120gms

questions.text: The sum of four consecutive numbers is 230. Find them.
questions.solution:
Let the number be x

The second consecutive number will be x+1

The third consecutive number will be x+2

The fourth consecutive number will be x+3

x+(x+1)+(x+2)+(x+3)=230

x+x+1+x+2+x+3=230

4x+6=230

4x=230-6

4x=224

x=$\frac{224}{4}$  

x=56

The first number =56

The second number =x+1=56+1=57

The third number = x+2=56+2=58

The fourth number =x+3=56+3=59

steps.step:
Let the number be x

The fourth number = x+3 = 56+3=59
